content.description: Same start as Shmangled and Dangled.  Sit start LOW on cool pinch/edge combo feature.  Up to good edge and bust out right. Finish up and right on cool little incuts.
content.location: North side of warmup boulder finishing right of Dangled.

content.description:
The mother of all link-ups on the warmup boulder AKA "The Big Dirty." Basically climb Jimbo Deluxe, but instead of finishing up Jimmy D keep going left turning the corner and finishing up either Hookin for Cheeseburgers or Randy-Bo-Bandy.

You got to love the Trailer Park Boys!
content.location: Rambo Rail start (No Big Mama Jug) traversing left into either Hookin for Cheeseburgers or Randy-Bo-Bandy.

content.description: Sit start LOW on a cool pinch/edge combo feature.  Up to good edges and either go big out left good hold or do the "shmangler move" and use a intermediate gaston. Finish up and left.
content.location: North side of warmup boulder. Leftmost route.

content.description: Sit start on rock right of Hookin for Cheeseburgers. Head up and right into cool fossilized looking jugs.
content.location: North face. Right of Hookin for Cheeseburgers. Sit start on rock.

content.description: An elimnate but, still good.  Start as per Catharsis and climb that problem to the pinch, but eliminate the huge jug you would normally toss to. Instead, use some creative footwork to reverse Rambo Rail until you are set up for the finish of Rambo Direct. Finish out Rambo Direct. Phewww that was a mouthful. So in summation, Catharsis (No Jug) into Rambo Direct.
content.location: Catharsis start into Rambo Direct finish. (Large Jug Off)

content.description: One of the best on the boulder. Sit start matched on low undercling in the overhang. Bust out left into the rail feature and ride that until you can do a big move out left to a huge jug. Match the jug and go for the summit!
Same start as Rambo Rail, but instead of doing the big move left to a jug go straight up to incut and go agian to a jug up and right. Good Movement.
content.location: South Face. Start matched on undercling in the small overhang.

content.description: Sit start right of Jimmy D/Bushwhackin with left hand pinch and small right hand crimp. Move right had to a flatty and left to the sinker jug/pocket. From here move left to another jug and either press straight up the center of the face or continue trending right up good edges.
content.location: Center of west face. Right of Jimmy D/Bushwhackin.

content.description: Tallest problem on the warmup boulder. Crouch start matched on left facing jug/flake. Go straight up through large holds staying left of small bush and finishing directly up the slab.
content.location: Red line on beta photo. Left most route on west face of the warmup boulder.

content.description: Link-up/eliminate, but fun none the less. Rambo Rail start (eliminating the large jug) into Jimmy D finish. Sounds stupid, but turning the corner without the big mama jug rquires some thought provoking sequences.
content.location: Rambo Rail start (No Jug) into Jimmy D finish.

content.description: This is a fun one! Sit start right of Polly Pocket on a right facing jug/flake. Make a big move left to a rounded jug, then trend right through good edges and nipples.
content.location: West Face. Right of Polly Pocket. Pink line in beta photo.

content.description: Link the Jimmy D start into Randy-Bo-Bandy.
content.location: Start on left facing jug/flake of Jimmy D. Go left around the arete and link into Randy-Bo-Bandy.

content.description: Start right of Wrangled either sitting or standing on a large rock.  Go up and left making big moves between good holds.
content.location: North Face. Right of Wrangled starting on the rock at the base of the boulder.

content.description: Same start as Shmangled.  Sit start LOW on pinch/edge combo feature. Up to good edges and go slightly right, but finish straight up directly over rock.
content.location: North side of warmup boulder. Same start as Shmangled, but finishing direct instead of left.

content.description: Same start as the Rambo Series, but with a different action star. Sit start matched on undercling in small overhang. Instead of going into the rail feature, go right to a incut sidepull and left hand nearby on small sidepull. Paste feet and chuck for a good hold just over the lip. Top it out.
content.protection: Pad or just fall in the bush.
content.location: South face. Same start hold as Rambo Rail, but go right.

content.description: Not too contrived with awesome movement! Same start as Natty Light. Sit start on right facing jug/flake. Move left hand to small crimpy pocket, right hand to incut crimper, and a big bump to a pinch. Toss to the jug and summit!
content.location: West Face. Same start as Natty Light, but heads right. White line in beta photo.

content.description: Classic warmup... Same start as Jimmy D. Crouch start matched on left facing jug/flake. Move up through large holds towards small bush. Head right of the bush, riding a rightward trending rail to the apex of the boulder!
content.location: West face. Same start as Jimmy D but breaking right at the small bush.

pathTokens: House of the Setting Sun (aka The Ammo Dump)
